  "text": "The bR Protein Is Inserted within NLP Membrane-bR⅐NLPs from cell-free co-expression and NLPs assembled by conventional means [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] were both examined by AFM to assess NLP size and shape and to demonstrate the association between bR with NLPs. For comparison with cell-free produced bR⅐NLP complexes, both bR⅐NLPs and empty NLPs were also prepared using methods described previously [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . These NLPs and bR⅐NLP complexes were made with apolipoprotein A-I (⌬1-55) or ⌬55A1 (MSP1T2, Nanodisc Inc.), purple membrane bR, and DMPC liposomes [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . Both the co-expressed and conventionally assembled bR⅐NLPs showed similar 1.4-nm increases in particle height relative to an empty NLP indicating likely association of bR protein within the NLPs (Fig. 4) .",
